WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:19.937
PulseProof explains why a match moment matters—and makes the memory verifiable.

00:00:19.937 --> 00:00:39.873
The public product clearly separates live TxLINE coverage from labelled replay data.

00:00:39.873 --> 00:01:00.279
Plan, follow, catch up and remember—from one trusted matchday companion.

00:01:00.279 --> 00:01:21.761
Catch-up reveals only the event prefix already watched—never the future score.

00:01:21.761 --> 00:01:45.247
Real coverage is shown; missing competition or timing data stays unavailable.

00:01:45.247 --> 00:02:08.484
Finished-match Catch-up survives weak networks without caching the live feed.

00:02:08.484 --> 00:02:29.040
An evidence-bound moment becomes an anti-replay receipt, not a tradable asset.

00:02:29.040 --> 00:02:47.526
The same test wallet has a finalized, Explorer-visible devnet claim.

00:02:47.526 --> 00:03:10.282
Every field is bound, every receipt is unique, and every proof expires quickly.

00:03:10.282 --> 00:03:33.153
Seventy-nine tests, zero known vulnerabilities, green CI and public devnet evidence.

00:03:33.153 --> 00:03:49.084
A public GitHub Actions run verifies a production commit deployed to Railway.

00:03:49.084 --> 00:04:13.765
Free for fans; sustainable through partner rooms, analytics and consented loyalty.

